rldot1xExtAuthSessionStatsTable.name: rldot1xExtAuthSessionStatsTable
rldot1xExtAuthSessionStatsTable.description: A table that contains the session statistics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each Port. An entry appears in this table for each port that may authenticate access to itself.

rldot1xExtAuthSessionStatsEntry.name: rldot1xExtAuthSessionStatsEntry
rldot1xExtAuthSessionStatsEntry.description: The session statistics information for an Authenticator PAE. This shows the current values being collected for each session that is still in progress, or the final values for the last valid session on each port where there is no session currently active.

rlDot1xAuthSessionAuthenticMethod.name: rlDot1xAuthSessionAuthenticMethod

rldot1xAuthenticationPortTable.name: rldot1xAuthenticationPortTable
rldot1xAuthenticationPortTable.description: A table of system level information for each port supported by the Port Access Entity. An entry appears in this table for each port of this system.

rldot1xAuthenticationPortEntry.name: rldot1xAuthenticationPortEntry
rldot1xAuthenticationPortEntry.description: The Port number and mac method

rldot1xAuthenticationPortMethod.name: rldot1xAuthenticationPortMethod
rldot1xAuthenticationPortMethod.description: The value of the mac based authenication.

rldot1xRadiusAttrVlanIdEnabled.name: rldot1xRadiusAttrVlanIdEnabled
rldot1xRadiusAttrVlanIdEnabled.description: Defines if treat VLAN ID that received from Radius attributes in Radius-Accept message.

rldot1xRadiusAttAclNameEnabled.name: rldot1xRadiusAttAclNameEnabled
rldot1xRadiusAttAclNameEnabled.description: Defines if treat ACL Names that received from Radius attributes in Radius-Accept message.

rldot1xTimeBasedName.name: rldot1xTimeBasedName
rldot1xTimeBasedName.description: Specifies a time range. When the Time Range is not in effect the port state would be Unauthorized.

rldot1xTimeBasedActive.name: rldot1xTimeBasedActive
rldot1xTimeBasedActive.description: Specifies if time range is active now or not.

rldot1xRadiusAttrVlanIdentifier.name: rldot1xRadiusAttrVlanIdentifier
rldot1xRadiusAttrVlanIdentifier.description: In case that value is not 0, This field will define the VLAN ID in case that it is not received from Radius attributes in Radius-Accept message.

rldot1xAuthMultiStatsTable.name: rldot1xAuthMultiStatsTable
rldot1xAuthMultiStatsTable.description: A table that contains the statistics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each Port and MAC for multisession 802.1x mode of operation. An entry appears in this table for each port and MAC that have an authentication session currently running under way for them.

rldot1xAuthMultiStatsEntry.name: rldot1xAuthMultiStatsEntry
rldot1xAuthMultiStatsEntry.description: The statistics information for an Authenticator PAE.

rldot1xAuthMultiEapolFramesRx.name: rldot1xAuthMultiEapolFramesRx
rldot1xAuthMultiEapolFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAPOL frames of any type that have been received by this Authenticator.

rldot1xAuthMultiEapolFramesTx.name: rldot1xAuthMultiEapolFramesTx
rldot1xAuthMultiEapolFramesTx.description: The number of EAPOL frames of any type that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

rldot1xAuthMultiEapolStartFramesRx.name: rldot1xAuthMultiEapolStartFramesRx
rldot1xAuthMultiEapolStartFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Start frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

rldot1xAuthMultiEapolLogoffFramesRx.name: rldot1xAuthMultiEapolLogoffFramesRx
rldot1xAuthMultiEapolLogoffFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Logoff frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

rldot1xAuthMultiEapolRespIdFramesRx.name: rldot1xAuthMultiEapolRespIdFramesRx
rldot1xAuthMultiEapolRespIdFramesRx.description: The number of EAP Resp/Id frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

rldot1xAuthMultiEapolRespFramesRx.name: rldot1xAuthMultiEapolRespFramesRx
rldot1xAuthMultiEapolRespFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAP Response frames (other than Resp/Id frames) that have been received by this Authenticator.

rldot1xAuthMultiEapolReqIdFramesTx.name: rldot1xAuthMultiEapolReqIdFramesTx
rldot1xAuthMultiEapolReqIdFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Req/Id frames that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

rldot1xAuthMultiEapolReqFramesTx.name: rldot1xAuthMultiEapolReqFramesTx
rldot1xAuthMultiEapolReqFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Request frames (other than Rq/Id frames) that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

rldot1xAuthMultiInvalidEapolFramesRx.name: rldot1xAuthMultiInvalidEapolFramesRx
rldot1xAuthMultiInvalidEapolFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator in which the frame type is not recognized.

rldot1xAuthMultiEapLengthErrorFramesRx.name: rldot1xAuthMultiEapLengthErrorFramesRx
rldot1xAuthMultiEapLengthErrorFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator in which the Packet Body Length field is invalid.

rldot1xAuthMultiDiagTable.name: rldot1xAuthMultiDiagTable
rldot1xAuthMultiDiagTable.description: A table that contains the diagnostics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each Port and MAC. An entry appears in this table for each port and MAC that have an authentication session currently running under way for them.

rldot1xAuthMultiDiagEntry.name: rldot1xAuthMultiDiagEntry
rldot1xAuthMultiDiagEntry.description: The diagnostics information for an Authenticator PAE.

rldot1xAuthMultiEntersConnecting.name: rldot1xAuthMultiEntersConnecting
rldot1xAuthMultiEntersConnecting.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions to the CONNECTING state from any other state.

rldot1xAuthMultiEntersAuthenticating.name: rldot1xAuthMultiEntersAuthenticating
rldot1xAuthMultiEntersAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from CONNECTING to AUTHENTICATING, as a result of an EAP-Response/Identity message being received from the Supplicant.

rldot1xAuthMultiAuthSuccessWhileAuthenti.name: rldot1xAuthMultiAuthSuccessWhileAuthenticating
rldot1xAuthMultiAuthSuccessWhileAuthenti.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to AUTHENTICATED, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating successful authentication of the Supplicant (authSuccess = TRUE).

rldot1xAuthMultiAuthFailWhileAuthenticat.name: rldot1xAuthMultiAuthFailWhileAuthenticating
rldot1xAuthMultiAuthFailWhileAuthenticat.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to HELD, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating authentication failure (authFail = TRUE).

rldot1xAuthMultiAuthReauthsWhileAuthenti.name: rldot1xAuthMultiAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticating
rldot1xAuthMultiAuthReauthsWhileAuthenti.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of a reauthentication request (reAuthenticate = TRUE).

rldot1xAuthMultiAuthEapStartsWhileAuthen.name: rldot1xAuthMultiAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticating
rldot1xAuthMultiAuthEapStartsWhileAuthen.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Start message being received from the Supplicant.

rldot1xAuthMultiAuthReauthsWhileAuthenti.name: rldot1xAuthMultiAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticated
rldot1xAuthMultiAuthReauthsWhileAuthenti.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to CONNECTING, as a result of a reauthentication request (reAuthenticate = TRUE).

rldot1xAuthMultiAuthEapStartsWhileAuthen.name: rldot1xAuthMultiAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticated
rldot1xAuthMultiAuthEapStartsWhileAuthen.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to CONNECTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Start message being received from the Supplicant.

rldot1xAuthMultiBackendResponses.name: rldot1xAuthMultiBackendResponses
rldot1xAuthMultiBackendResponses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an initial Access-Request packet to the Authentication server (i.e., executes sendRespToServer on entry to the RESPONSE state). Indicates that the Authenticator attempted communication with the Authentication Server.

rldot1xAuthMultiBackendAccessChallenges.name: rldot1xAuthMultiBackendAccessChallenges
rldot1xAuthMultiBackendAccessChallenges.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an initial Access-Challenge packet from the Authentication server (i.e., aReq becomes TRUE, causing exit from the RESPONSE state). Indicates that the Authentication Server has communication with the Authenticator.

rldot1xAuthMultiBackendOtherRequestsToSu.name: rldot1xAuthMultiBackendOtherRequestsToSupplicant
rldot1xAuthMultiBackendOtherRequestsToSu.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an EAP-Request packet (other than an Identity, Notification, Failure or Success message) to the Supplicant (i.e., executes txReq on entry to the REQUEST state). Indicates that the Authenticator chose an EAP-method.

rldot1xAuthMultiBackendNonNakResponsesFr.name: rldot1xAuthMultiBackendNonNakResponsesFromSupplicant
rldot1xAuthMultiBackendNonNakResponsesFr.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives a response from the Supplicant to an initial EAP-Request, and the response is something other than EAP-NAK (i.e., rxResp becomes TRUE, causing the state machine to transition from REQUEST to RESPONSE, and the response is not an EAP-NAK). Indicates that the Supplicant can respond to the Authenticators chosen EAP-method.

rldot1xAuthMultiBackendAuthSuccesses.name: rldot1xAuthMultiBackendAuthSuccesses
rldot1xAuthMultiBackendAuthSuccesses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Success message from the Authentication Server (i.e., aSuccess becomes TRUE, causing a transition from RESPONSE to SUCCESS). Indicates that the Supplicant has successfully authenticated to the Authentication Server.

rldot1xAuthMultiSessionFramesRx.name: rldot1xAuthMultiSessionFramesRx

rldot1xAuthMultiSessionFramesTx.name: rldot1xAuthMultiSessionFramesTx
rldot1xAuthMultiSessionFramesTx.description: The number of user data frames transmitted on this Port during the session.

rldot1xAuthMultiSessionId.name: rldot1xAuthMultiSessionId
rldot1xAuthMultiSessionId.description: A unique identifier for the session, in the form of a printable ASCII string of at least three characters.

rldot1xAuthMultiSessionTime.name: rldot1xAuthMultiSessionTime

rldot1xAuthMultiSessionUserName.description: The User-Name representing the identity of the Supplicant PAE.

rldot1xAuthMultiSessionRadiusAttrVlan.description: VLAN ID that received from Radius attributes.

rldot1xAuthMultiConfigTable.description: A table that contains the configuration objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each port and MAC. An entry appears in this table for each port and MAC that may authenticate access to itself.

rldot1xAuthMultiConfigEntry.description: The configuration information for an Authenticator PAE.

rldot1xAuthMultiPaeState.name: rldot1xAuthMultiPaeState
rldot1xAuthMultiPaeState.description: The current value of the Authenticator PAE state machine.

rldot1xAuthMultiBackendAuthState.name: rldot1xAuthMultiBackendAuthState
rldot1xAuthMultiBackendAuthState.description: The current state of the Backend Authentication state machine.

rldot1xAuthMultiControlledPortStatus.description: The current value of the controlled Port status parameter for the Port.

rldot1xBpduFilteringEnabled.description: Specify that when 802.1x is globally disabled, 802.1x BPDU packets would be filtered or bridged.

rldot1xGuestVlanTimeInterval.description: indicate the guest vlan timeout interval.

rldot1xMacAuthSuccessTrapEnabled.description: Specify if sending traps when a MAC address is successfully authenticated by the 802.1X mac-authentication access control.

rldot1xMacAuthFailureTrapEnabled.description: Specify if sending traps when MAC address was failed in authentication of the 802.1X MAC authentication access control.
